This paper is about program synthesis, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach proposed in the paper involves using graph reachability and abstraction refinement, which are techniques commonly used in formal methods and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the implementation of the approach in a tool, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with type-directed synthesis, which is related to type theory and functional programming (cs.FL).
